SD=Special Pricing Conditions
CR=Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
BQs= PricingTerms
This service domain allows the bank to apply special pricing terms and conditions that override standard price calculations. These override facilities are to be used in specific situations where a bank level decision is taken to amend prices or pricing terms in response to some major event or business development action
The bank suspends certain product fees during a major brand awareness campaign
Maintain a pricing list or conditions (with ranges and optional terms) categorized by various dimensions to impose exceptional product pricing conditions that override standard pricing terms (for special events/situations)
CR - Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry							BQ - Pricing Terms		
In	Up	Co	Ec	Ex	Rq	Re	In	Up	Re
InCR Instantiate a new Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
UpCR Update details relating to Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
CoCR Control the processing of Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
EcCR Accept, verify, etc. aspects of Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry processing
ExCR Execute an available automated action for Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
RqCR Request manual intervention or a decision with respect to Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
ReCR Retrieve details about any aspect of Special Pricing Conditions Directory Entry
InBQ Instantiate a new Pricing Terms
UpBQ Update details relating to Pricing Terms
ReBQ Retrieve details about any aspect of Pricing Terms